      "extra": {
        "message": "Missing Rate Limiting on Signup Endpoint\n\nThe do_signup() handler at POST /signup has no rate limiting, allowing unlimited registration attempts. This enables brute-force attacks against registration codes.\n\nImpact: An attacker can brute-force registration codes to create unauthorized accounts. The static code 'a36e990b-0024-4d55-b74a-f8d7528e1764' in db_seed.py makes this even more exploitable.\n\nFix: Implement rate limiting on the signup endpoint.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-307"
          ],
          "finding_id": "b85c68b2-49c2-45ba-9365-77301221578e"
        }
