      "extra": {
        "message": "SQLAlchemy Echo Mode Exposes SQL Queries in Logs\n\nThe SQLAlchemy engine is configured with echo=True, which logs all SQL statements including potentially sensitive data in query parameters to stdout/stderr. This can expose PII and other sensitive information in production logs.\n\nImpact: SQL queries containing user data (emails, search terms, note content) are logged to stdout, potentially exposing PII in log aggregation systems.\n\nFix: Set echo=False in production or use environment-based configuration to only enable SQL logging in development.",
        "severity": "MEDIUM",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-200"
          ],
          "finding_id": "87a6e6eb-075e-47d0-b066-a33bf9e389b4"
        }
      }
    },
